Volume 2933 of the series Lecture Notes in Computer Science pp 250-268 A Linear-Time Solution to the Knapsack Problem Using P Systems with Active Membranes Mario J. Pérez-Jiménez Affiliated with Dpto. de Ciencias de la Computación e Inteligencia Artificial, E.T.S. Ingeniería Informática, Universidad de Sevilla , Agustin Riscos-Núñez Affiliated with Dpto. de Ciencias de la Computación e Inteligencia Artificial, E.T.S. Ingeniería Informática, Universidad de Sevilla Up to now, P systems dealing with numerical problems have been rarely considered in the literature. In this paper we present an effective solution to the Knapsack problem using a family of deterministic P systems with active membranes using 2-division. We show that the number of steps of any computation is of linear order, but polynomial time is required for pre-computing resources.